            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EThe%20power%20of%20God%20is%20tangible!%20Elisha%20had%20been%20buried%20for%20an%20undetermined%20period%20of%20time%20when%20another%20dead%20man%20was%20accidentally%20thrown%20into%20his%20grave.%20Elisha's%20bones%20had%20so%20much%20of%20the%20power%20of%20God%20still%20residing%20in%20them%20that%20they%20caused%20the%20dead%20man%20to%20resurrect.%20And%20to%20think%2C%20we%20have%20trouble%20raising%20the%20dead%20while%20we%20are%20still%20alive!%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EPaul's%20body%20also%20contained%20great%20power%20from%20God.%20Even%20handkerchiefs%20that%20he%20had%20touched%20could%20be%20taken%20to%20the%20sick%20to%20bring%20healing%20(Acts%2019%3A11-12).%20Obviously%2C%20Jesus%20carried%20this%20power%2C%20too.%20People%20could%20touch%20the%20hem%20of%20His%20garment%20and%20be%20completely%20healed.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EIn%20each%20of%20these%20cases%2C%20the%20power%20of%20God%20inhabited%20the%20physical%20world%20and%20was%20able%20to%20be%20transmitted.%20Why%20should%20we%20think%20it%20strange%20that%20God's%20supernatural%2C%20miracle-working%20power%20can%20break%20into%20the%20physical%20world%20and%20change%20even%20the%20most%20desperate%20of%20circumstances%3F%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EIf%20we%20are%20filled%20with%20the%20Holy%20Spirit%2C%20this%20same%20power%20is%20in%20us.%20We%20must%20exercise%20it%20to%20minister%20justice%20to%20the%20oppressed%2C%20provide%20food%20for%20the%20hungry%2C%20and%20bring%20freedom%20to%20the%20captives%20(Psalm%20146%3A7).%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
            "id": "ot-passage",
