            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "2Kgs.13:1-14:29",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3E2%20Kings%2013%3A1-14%3A29%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_13_1%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E2%20Kings%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EJehoahaz%20Rules%20in%20Israel%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EJehoahaz%20son%20of%20Jehu%20began%20to%20rule%20over%20Israel%20in%20the%20twenty-third%20year%20of%20King%20Joash%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%20in%20Judah.%20He%20reigned%20in%20Samaria%20seventeen%20years.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_13_2%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20he%20did%20what%20was%20evil%20in%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20sight.%20He%20followed%20the%20example%20of%20Jeroboam%20son%20of%20Nebat%2C%20continuing%20the%20sins%20that%20Jeroboam%20had%20led%20Israel%20to%20commit.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_13_3%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20was%20very%20angry%20with%20Israel%2C%20and%20he%20allowed%20King%20Hazael%20of%20Aram%20and%20his%20son%20Ben-hadad%20to%20defeat%20them%20repeatedly.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_13_4%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Jehoahaz%20prayed%20for%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20help%2C%20and%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20heard%20his%20prayer%2C%20for%20he%20could%20see%20how%20severely%20the%20king%20of%20Aram%20was%20oppressing%20Israel.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_13_5%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20provided%20someone%20to%20rescue%20the%20Israelites%20from%20the%20tyranny%20of%20the%20Arameans.%20Then%20Israel%20lived%20in%20safety%20again%20as%20they%20had%20in%20former%20days.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_13_6%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20they%20continued%20to%20sin%2C%20following%20the%20evil%20example%20of%20Jeroboam.%20They%20also%20allowed%20the%20Asherah%20pole%20in%20Samaria%20to%20remain%20standing.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_13_7%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EFinally%2C%20Jehoahaz%26%23x2019%3Bs%20army%20was%20reduced%20to%2050%26%23xA0%3Bcharioteers%2C%2010%26%23xA0%3Bchariots%2C%20and%2010%2C000%20foot%20soldiers.%20The%20king%20of%20Aram%20had%20killed%20the%20others%2C%20trampling%20them%20like%20dust%20under%20his%20feet.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_13_8%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20rest%20of%20the%20events%20in%20Jehoahaz%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%26%23x2014%3Beverything%20he%20did%20and%20the%20extent%20of%20his%20power%26%23x2014%3Bare%20recorded%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Book%20of%20the%20History%20of%20the%20Kings%20of%20Israel.%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_13_9%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Jehoahaz%20died%2C%20he%20was%20buried%20in%20Samaria.%20Then%20his%20son%20Jehoash%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E13%3A9%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EJoash%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20variant%20spelling%20of%20Jehoash%3B%20also%20in%2013%3A10%2C%2012%2C%2013%2C%2014%2C%2025.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20became%20the%20next%20king.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_13_10%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EJehoash%20Rules%20in%20Israel%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EJehoash%20son%20of%20Jehoahaz%20began%20to%20rule%20over%20Israel%20in%20the%20thirty-seventh%20year%20of%20King%20Joash%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%20in%20Judah.%20He%20reigned%20in%20Samaria%20sixteen%20years.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_13_11%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20he%20did%20what%20was%20evil%20in%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20sight.%20He%20refused%20to%20turn%20from%20the%20sins%20that%20Jeroboam%20son%20of%20Nebat%20had%20led%20Israel%20to%20commit.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_13_12%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20rest%20of%20the%20events%20in%20Jehoash%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%20and%20everything%20he%20did%2C%20including%20the%20extent%20of%20his%20power%20and%20his%20war%20with%20King%20Amaziah%20of%20Judah%2C%20are%20recorded%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Book%20of%20the%20History%20of%20the%20Kings%20of%20Israel.%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_13_13%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Jehoash%20died%2C%20he%20was%20buried%20in%20Samaria%20with%20the%20kings%20of%20Israel.%20Then%20his%20son%20Jeroboam%26%23xA0%3BII%20became%20the%20next%20king.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_13_14%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EElisha%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Final%20Prophecy%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Elisha%20was%20in%20his%20last%20illness%2C%20King%20Jehoash%20of%20Israel%20visited%20him%20and%20wept%20over%20him.%20%26%23x201C%3BMy%20father!%20My%20father!%20I%20see%20the%20chariots%20and%20charioteers%20of%20Israel!%26%23x201D%3B%20he%20cried.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_13_15%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EElisha%20told%20him%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BGet%20a%20bow%20and%20some%20arrows.%26%23x201D%3B%20And%20the%20king%20did%20as%20he%20was%20told.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_13_16%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EElisha%20told%20him%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BPut%20your%20hand%20on%20the%20bow%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20and%20Elisha%20laid%20his%20own%20hands%20on%20the%20king%26%23x2019%3Bs%20hands.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_13_17%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20he%20commanded%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BOpen%20that%20eastern%20window%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20and%20he%20opened%20it.%20Then%20he%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BShoot!%26%23x201D%3B%20So%20he%20shot%20an%20arrow.%20Elisha%20proclaimed%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BThis%20is%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20arrow%2C%20an%20arrow%20of%20victory%20over%20Aram%2C%20for%20you%20will%20completely%20conquer%20the%20Arameans%20at%20Aphek.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_13_18%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20he%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BNow%20pick%20up%20the%20other%20arrows%20and%20strike%20them%20against%20the%20ground.%26%23x201D%3B%20So%20the%20king%20picked%20them%20up%20and%20struck%20the%20ground%20three%20times.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_13_19%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20the%20man%20of%20God%20was%20angry%20with%20him.%20%26%23x201C%3BYou%20should%20have%20struck%20the%20ground%20five%20or%20six%20times!%26%23x201D%3B%20he%20exclaimed.%20%26%23x201C%3BThen%20you%20would%20have%20beaten%20Aram%20until%20it%20was%20entirely%20destroyed.%20Now%20you%20will%20be%20victorious%20only%20three%20times.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_13_20%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Elisha%20died%20and%20was%20buried.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3EGroups%20of%20Moabite%20raiders%20used%20to%20invade%20the%20land%20each%20spring.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_13_21%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3EOnce%20when%20some%20Israelites%20were%20burying%20a%20man%2C%20they%20spied%20a%20band%20of%20these%20raiders.%20So%20they%20hastily%20threw%20the%20corpse%20into%20the%20tomb%20of%20Elisha%20and%20fled.%20But%20as%20soon%20as%20the%20body%20touched%20Elisha%26%23x2019%3Bs%20bones%2C%20the%20dead%20man%20revived%20and%20jumped%20to%20his%20feet!%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_13_22%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2222%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3EKing%20Hazael%20of%20Aram%20had%20oppressed%20Israel%20during%20the%20entire%20reign%20of%20King%20Jehoahaz.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_13_23%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E23%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20was%20gracious%20and%20merciful%20to%20the%20people%20of%20Israel%2C%20and%20they%20were%20not%20totally%20destroyed.%20He%20pitied%20them%20because%20of%20his%20covenant%20with%20Abraham%2C%20Isaac%2C%20and%20Jacob.%20And%20to%20this%20day%20he%20still%20has%20not%20completely%20destroyed%20them%20or%20banished%20them%20from%20his%20presence.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_13_24%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2224%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E24%3C%2Fspan%3EKing%20Hazael%20of%20Aram%20died%2C%20and%20his%20son%20Ben-hadad%20became%20the%20next%20king.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_13_25%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E25%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Jehoash%20son%20of%20Jehoahaz%20recaptured%20from%20Ben-hadad%20son%20of%20Hazael%20the%20towns%20that%20had%20been%20taken%20from%20Jehoash%26%23x2019%3Bs%20father%2C%20Jehoahaz.%20Jehoash%20defeated%20Ben-hadad%20on%20three%20occasions%2C%20and%20he%20recovered%20the%20Israelite%20towns.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_14_1%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2214%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E2%20Kings%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EAmaziah%20Rules%20in%20Judah%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EAmaziah%20son%20of%20Joash%20began%20to%20rule%20over%20Judah%20in%20the%20second%20year%20of%20the%20reign%20of%20King%20Jehoash%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E14%3A1%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EJoash%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20variant%20spelling%20of%20Jehoash%3B%20also%20in%2014%3A13%2C%2023%2C%2027.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20of%20Israel.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_14_2%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2214%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EAmaziah%20was%20twenty-five%20years%20old%20when%20he%20became%20king%2C%20and%20he%20reigned%20in%20Jerusalem%20twenty-nine%20years.%20His%20mother%20was%20Jehoaddin%20from%20Jerusalem.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_14_3%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2214%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EAmaziah%20did%20what%20was%20pleasing%20in%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20sight%2C%20but%20not%20like%20his%20ancestor%20David.%20Instead%2C%20he%20followed%20the%20example%20of%20his%20father%2C%20Joash.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_14_4%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2214%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EAmaziah%20did%20not%20destroy%20the%20pagan%20shrines%2C%20and%20the%20people%20still%20offered%20sacrifices%20and%20burned%20incense%20there.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_14_5%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2214%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Amaziah%20was%20well%20established%20as%20king%2C%20he%20executed%20the%20officials%20who%20had%20assassinated%20his%20father.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_14_6%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2214%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EHowever%2C%20he%20did%20not%20kill%20the%20children%20of